swDHCPServerMIB.name: swDHCPServerMIB
swDHCPServerMIB.description: The structure of DHCP Server management for the proprietary enterprise.

swDHCPServerState.name: swDHCPServerState
swDHCPServerState.description: This object enables/disables the DHCP server status of the device.

swDHCPServerPingPktNumber.name: swDHCPServerPingPktNumber
swDHCPServerPingPktNumber.description: This object specifies the number of ping packets the DHCP server sends to an IP address before assigning this address to a requesting client. 0 means no ping test.

swDHCPServerPingTimeOut.name: swDHCPServerPingTimeOut
swDHCPServerPingTimeOut.description: This object specifies the amount of time in millisecond the DHCP server must wait before timing out a ping packet.

swDHCPServerLogState.name: swDHCPServerLogState
swDHCPServerLogState.description: This object enables/disables the DHCP server log status of the device.

swDHCPServerExcludedAddressTable.name: swDHCPServerExcludedAddressTable
swDHCPServerExcludedAddressTable.description: A table that contains an IP addresses group that the DHCP server should not assign to DHCP client.

swDHCPServerExcludedAddressEntry.name: swDHCPServerExcludedAddressEntry
swDHCPServerExcludedAddressEntry.description: A group of IP addresses that the DHCP server should not assign to DHCP client.

swDHCPServerExcludedAddressBegin.name: swDHCPServerExcludedAddressBegin
swDHCPServerExcludedAddressBegin.description: The start address of this address range.

swDHCPServerExcludedAddressEnd.name: swDHCPServerExcludedAddressEnd
swDHCPServerExcludedAddressEnd.description: The end address of this address range.

swDHCPServerPoolLeaseState.description: The pool lease state. When configured to infinity, the following nodes include swDHCPServerPoolLeaseDay, swDHCPServerPoolLeaseHour and swDHCPServerPoolLeaseMinute have no significance any more.

swDHCPServerDNSServerAddress.description: The IP address of a DNS server that is available to a DHCP client.

swDHCPServerManualBindingEntry.description: A list of manual pool binding.

swDHCPServerManualBindingPoolName.description: The pool name of this entry.

swDHCPServerManualBindingIpAddress.description: IP address which will be assigned to specified client.

swDHCPServerManualBindingType.description: The type of this manual binding. both(3): The client type has no significance, the entry could apply to either one.

swDHCPServerBindingTable.description: A table that contains information regarding dynamic binding information of a pool of IP addresses.

swDHCPServerBindingPoolName.description: The name of this pool entry.

swDHCPServerBindingClearState.description: This object is used to clear this entry.

swDHCPServerConflictIPTable.name: swDHCPServerConflictIPTable

swDHCPServerConflictIPEntry.description: A DHCP address conflict means a duplication of use of the same IP address by two hosts.

swDHCPServerConflictIPIPAddress.description: IP address which is duplicated and used by two hosts.

swDHCPServerConflictIPDetectionMethod.description: The server detects conflicts using ping. The client detects conflicts using gratuitous Address Resolution Protocol (ARP).

swDHCPServerConflictIPDetectionTime.description: The time at which a DHCP address conflict happens.

swDHCPServerClassEntry.description: A list of information indicates the current DHCP class option configurations.

swDHCPServerClassOption.description: DHCP server class configured options. Now, it only supports option 60, 61, 82 and 125. 60: vendor class identifier; 61: client-identifier; 82: relay agent information option; 125: vendor-identifying vendor-specific information.

swDHCPServerClassOptionType.description: This object indicates the type of option. string(1): Means the type of option value is character string, it depends on swDHCPServerClassOptionValue. hex(2): Means the type of option value is hexadecimal, it depends on swDHCPServerClassOptionValue.

swDHCPServerClassOptionValue.description: This object indicates the value of this option.

swDHCPServerProfileEntry.description: A list of information indicates the current DHCP option profile.

swDHCPServerOptionTable.description: This table indicates the current DHCP option profile configurations.

swDHCPServerOptionEntry.name: swDHCPServerOptionEntry
swDHCPServerOptionEntry.description: A list of information indicates the current DHCP option profile configurations.

swDHCPServerOptionCode.name: swDHCPServerOptionCode
swDHCPServerOptionCode.description: DHCP server option profile configured options. Must not configure follow: 53:DHCP Message Type 54:Server Identifier Should not configure follow optoin that can configure through swDHCPServerPoolTable: 1:Subnet Mask (swDHCPServerPoolNetworkAddress and swDHCPServerPoolNetworkAddressMask) 3:Router Option (swDHCPServerDefaultRouterTable) 6:Domain Name Server (swDHCPServerNetBIOSNameServerTable) 15:Domain Name (swDHCPServerPoolDomainName) 44:Netbios Name Server (swDHCPServerNetBIOSNameServerTable) 46:Netbios Node Type (swDHCPServerPoolNetBIOSNodeType) 51/58/59:IP Address Lease Time/Renewal (T1) Time Value/Rebinding (T2) Time Value (swDHCPServerPoolLeaseState,swDHCPServerPoolLeaseDay, swDHCPServerPoolLeaseHour and swDHCPServerPoolLeaseMinute)

swDHCPServerOptionValueType.name: swDHCPServerOptionValueType
swDHCPServerOptionValueType.description: This object indicates the type of option. string(1): Means the type of option value is character string, it depends on swDHCPServerOptionProfileOptionValue. hex(2): Means the type of option value is hexadecimal, it depends on swDHCPServerOptionProfileOptionValue.
